text: Bakhcha () is a rural locality (a village) in Karagushsky Selsoviet, Sterlibashevsky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 92 as of 2010. There are 2 streets. == Geography == It is located 16 km from Sterlibashevo, 3 km from Karagush. == References == Category:Rural localities in Sterlibashevsky District
title: Bakhcha, Sterlibashevsky District, Republic of Bashkortostan
